Ambassador John Bolton and National Security Advisor Sheikh Tahnoon of the United Arab Emirates had a phone conversation in which they discussed their commitment to advancing shared American and Emirati interests. Sheikh Tahnoon congratulated Ambassador Bolton on his recent appointment and expressed his appreciation for the United Arab Emirates' efforts in fighting extremism and terrorism. Ambassador Bolton recognized the sacrifices made by Emirati soldiers and diplomats in this fight. They also discussed the historic cooperation between the United States and the United Arab Emirates in countering terrorism and aggression, as well as regional developments in Syria, Iran, and Yemen. They agreed to coordinate closely to enhance the strategic partnership between the two countries on these important issues.